Six people were injured when two minibus taxis collided on Main Road in Edendale, Pietermaritzburg on Saturday, paramedics said.
When ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene just before noon, they found two minibus taxis on the side of the road, ER24 spokeswoman Ineke van Huyssteen said.
Upon further assessment, paramedics found that six people had been injured, none seriously. ER24, as well as another medical service on the scene transported the patients to hospital for further medical care.
The cause of the crash was still unknown, Van Huyssteen said.
